articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Two former referees have accused Rangers and the Scottish FA of failing to appropriately punish Craig McPherson for his apparent headbutt on Celtic Women manager Fran Alonso.
articles.title: Rangers and SFA slammed over 'lenient' response to Craig McPherson Celtic headbutt

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Statistics are not the be-all-and-end-all when it comes to rating football teams and players, but two under-played Celtic and Rangers stars are the surprise names at the top of one Scottish Premiership metric this season.
articles.title: The surprise Celtic and Rangers duo topping the charts for goals created per 90 minutes

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: Joey Barton is keen to prove himself in Scotland after his failed time at Rangers which has left him viewed as a flop – meaning a possible stint as manager of Aberdeen, Hearts or Hibs.
articles.title: 'Only exception is with Rangers' - Joey Barton makes Hibs, Aberdeen or Hearts claim to ram it down Old Firm

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Matt O’Riley believes Celtic have maintained their peak performance levels for weeks as they look to tie up the cinch Premiership title as quickly as possible.
articles.title: Celtic baulk at peak performance talk - 'I think we’ve been at a good level for a long time'

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Kilmarnock forward Kyle Vassell was understandably downbeat after being involved in his team’s 4-1 defeat by Celtic. They are in a relegation battle and a heavy loss is not good for their points tally, goal difference or morale.
articles.title: Why Celtic are like a Premier League team - and the player who is 'so, so good at football'

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: The Celtic dressingroom is clearly consists of some exceptionally talented football players, but as anyone within football will testify, you need far more than just that to be successful.
articles.title: Inside the Celtic dressingroom: Unique group, friends, 'the nicest man I've ever met'

articles.author: Ross McLeish
articles.description: Ajax are the latest club to be linked with a move for Celtic forward Liel Abada.
articles.title: Ajax linked with Celtic forward Liel Abada as queue of suitors lengthens

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: We pick out three talking points from Celtic’s 4-1 win over Kilmarnock at Rugby Park.
articles.title: Celtic reaction: A Kyogo Furuhashi first, scouts in house but were Leverkusen there, Ben Summers 'growth'

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Celtic are making this title-winning malarkey look oh-so-easy. Another week, another opponent, another straightforward victory on their march to the Premiership crown. This 4-1 triumph away at Kilmarnock took their points tally to 91 and they broke the 100-goal mark in this match.
articles.title: Celtic's Sunday stroll in Ayrshire: the boa constrictor, Ange conducts fans, why coaches deserve so much praise

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Celtic manager Ange Postecoglou feels his team played some of their best football of the season during the 4-1 win over Kilmarnock and hailed his players’ desire to sprint to the title following this latest victory in the cinch Premiership.
articles.title: Ange Postecoglou explains why Celtic played 'best football of season' and singles out 'really good' newcomer

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Kilmarnock manager Derek McInnes lamented his team’s “car-crash start” against Celtic in conceding four goals, while also claiming that visiting striker Oh Hyeon-gyu should have been sent off later in the match after the 4-1 defeat at Rugby Park.
articles.title: Kilmarnock manager Derek McInnes claims Celtic player should have been red carded after 'car crash start'

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Jurgen Kilnsmann has revealed he travelled to Kilmarnock to watch Celtic striker Hyeung-gyu Oh after being blown away by the South Korea striker while on international duty.
articles.title: Jurgen Klinsmann breaks silence on Celtic visit and hails 'very special talent'

articles.author: Alan Pattullo
articles.description: An upcoming employment anniversary combined with a significant birthday prompted some wistful musing in a rare lull in play during last weekend’s breathless Old Firm match.
articles.title: Celtic v Rangers Old Firm fall-out is way beyond tedious - it's now dangerous

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Joe Hart has clearly found contentment at Celtic Park. Before moving to Glasgow, first-team football was hard to come by, warming the bench at Spurs and Burnley. Now he is a wanted man, a key part of a successful team dressing-room.
articles.title: Joe Hart relaxed on Celtic future as he answers queries over new deal with club

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Ange Postecoglou has confirmed he will not be indulging in the great British tradition of having a flutter on the Grand National on Saturday.
articles.title: Ange Postecoglou's Grand National tip as Celtic boss pins colours to mast ahead of potential Killie pie debut

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Hyeon-gyu Oh may have only started one of his nine Celtic appearances since his January arrival, but manager Ange Postecoglou is convinced that the South Korean is on the path to success.
articles.title: Celtic boss lifts lid on Hyeon-gyu Oh talks as Jurgen Klinsmann jets in on a special mission

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Alistair Johnston was already becoming a darling of the Celtic support, but his man-of-the-match performance in last weekend's win over Rangers has sent his reputation soaring.
articles.title: Alistair Johnston on Celtic fan adulation and why gap to Rangers could get bigger

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Celtic manager Ange Postecoglou has no fresh injury concerns for his team’s trip to Kilmarnock on Sunday.
articles.title: Celtic injury news may confirm Ange Postecoglou's thinking for Kilmarnock - predicted teams for Rugby Park clash

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Japan coach Hajime Moriyasu is planning to visit Celtic Park in the near future to watch the club’s cohort of Japanese players and hold talks with manager Ange Postecoglou.
articles.title: 'I was a little nervous': Japan coach plots trip and talks but admits early concern over Ange Postecoglou reaction

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Both Celtic manager Ange Postecoglou and his Rangers counterpart Michael Beale have commented on the abuse referee Kevin Clancy has received in the wake of last weekend’s Old Firm clash.
articles.title: Celtic and Rangers both react to Kevin Clancy abuse with strong comments
